Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Peel and chop the @red onion{1} into bite-sized chunks. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and chop into 3cm chunks. Chop the leafy green part and the base from the @leek{1} then chop it widthways into 1cm thick discs. Chop the @cherry tomatoes{1%pint} in half.

Toss the vegetables in @olive oil{1 1/2%tbsp} and a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook them on a #baking tray{} in the oven for ~{20%minutes}.

Dust the work surface with the @flour{about 100%g}, roll the @Northern Dough Co. pizza dough{2} out into round pizza shapes roughly 25cm across and place on a lightly oiled baking tray.

> Tip: If you don't have a rolling pin you can always use a wine bottle (or even a tin can at a push!).

Spread the @tomato purée{2%tbsp} thinly over each pizza base, leaving a border of around 2cm at the edge.

Once the veggies are soft and sweet divide them between each pizza base (making sure you only cover one half of each base, so you can fold the other half over). Turn your oven to maximum temperature. Tear the @mozzarella{1%ball} on top of the vegetables and sprinkle with @dried Italian herbs{1/2%tsp}.

> Tip: To prevent the pizza base getting soggy, be careful not to add any excess water from the vegetables.

Run a wet finger around the border of each pizza then fold them over. Press the edges down to seal and put on the top shelf of the oven for ~{8-10%minutes}. Job done!